<page no="384">
<section type="Arabian and Moorish Words">
<heading>
A briefe Table of sundrie Arabian and Moorish words vsuall in the Spanish tongue: all which as they stand dispersed in their seuerall places in the Dictionarie, are marked with a long Crosse, thus &#8224;.
</heading>
<wordgroup1 type="a" object="A"><alpha>A</alpha>  
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;ABah&#180;r,</form> <xpln lang="en"> to keepe in the reeke.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;Acical&#180;r,</form> <xpln lang="en"> to burnish or make trim.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;Acit&#180;ra,</form> <xpln lang="en"> a saddle tree, the railes on a wall.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;&#243;far,</form> <xpln lang="en"> brasse as it mined.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;or&#180;rse,</form> <xpln lang="en"> to waxe fierce or wilde.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;&#243;r,</form> <xpln lang="en"> a hauke.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;oz&#180;do,</form> <xpln lang="en"> wilde fierce.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;&#250;fre,</form> <xpln lang="en"> brimstone.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;&#250;mbre,</form> <xpln lang="en"> a measure holding three quarters.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;Acun&#231;&#180;r,</form> <xpln lang="en"> to polish, to trim vp.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;A&#231;ut&#233;a the roofe of a house,</form> <xpln lang="en"> flat leads of a house.</xpln></wordentry> 
<wordentry type="h"><form lang="ar">&#8224;Adah&#180;la,</form> <xpln lang="en"> that is giuen more than bar&#173;
gaine.</xpln></wordentry>
